  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and cook for 3 min on each side until golden, then add&nbsp;a splash of <strong>water </strong>and cook, covered, over a&nbsp;medium heat for 10-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>warm water</strong> in a small bowl until the sugar has dissolved &ndash; this is your <strong>sugar syrup</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>pecans</strong>&nbsp;to the <strong>sugar syrup</strong> and mix until coated&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once coated, add the <strong>pecans</strong> to one side of a baking tray&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1037.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tear the <strong>ciabatta roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>ciabatta</strong> to the other side of the baking tray, then drizzle it with<strong> olive oil</strong>, the <strong>dried&nbsp;oregano </strong>and&nbsp;a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 10-15 min &ndash; these are your<strong>&nbsp;candied pecans </strong>and<strong> oregano croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
